106A 101st Legislative Session 106
2026 South Dakota Legislature
Senate Bill 106
AMENDME NT 106A
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Senator Sauder
1 An Act to modify the amount required to be set aside for extraordinary expenses
2 incurred in providing special education programs.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That § 13-37-40 be AMENDED:
5 13-37-40. Subject to the limitation limitations provided below and in § 13-37-42,
6 the secretary of the Department of Education shall, for school fiscal year 2014 and each
7 year thereafter beginning July 1, 2026, set aside four five million dollars of the state aid
8 to districts for special education appropriation for extraordinary expenses incurred in
9 providing special education programs or services to one or more children with disabilities,
10 with expenditures to be made as recommended by an oversight board and approved by
11 the secretary of the Department of Education provided in § 13-37-60. Beginning July 1,
12 2027, and each year thereafter, the amount that the secretary shall set aside for
13 extraordinary expenses increases by the index factor, as defined in § 13-37-35.1.
14 Any funds not expended or obligated pursuant to this section shall are not be
15 subject to reversion pursuant to § 4-8-19. The total amount set aside for extraordinary
16 expenses each fiscal year plus the total amount not reverted from previous fiscal years
17 may, provided that the total amount reserved each year for extraordinary expenses does
18 not exceed five million five hundred thousand dollars.
19 The amount appropriated for extraordinary expenses shall be recalculated at the
20 same time as the amount of the allocations for disability levels as provided in § 13-37-
21 35.2. Beginning July 1, 2027, and each year thereafter, the maximum amount that may
22 be reserved for extraordinary expenses increases by the index factor, as defined in § 13-
23 37-35.1.
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

